
USE CASE DRAFT: T1562 Impair Defenses



ATTACK DESCRIPTION
Adversaries attempting to disable, modify, or bypass security controls to avoid detection and maintain persistence within a compromised environment. Relevant examples include disabling antivirus software, stopping logging services, clearing event logs, modifying firewall configurations, or terminating security monitoring tools.

ATT&CK Mapping
Technique: T1562 - Impair Defenses

Tactics:
- Defense Evasion
 

Detection Objective
Identify attempts to impair Windows security monitoring by detecting Security Event Log clearing activity, whcih may indicate an attacker attempting to remove evidence of malicious actions.

Potential Data Sources
- Windows Security Logs
- Event ID 1102(Security Log Cleared)
- Sysmon Process Creation Logs
- Windows Event Viewer
- Splunk SIEM

Detection Idea
Continously monitor Event ID 1102 within Windows Security Logs. Thsi event is generated whenever the Security Event Log is cleared and is considered a high-fidelity indicator of potential defense evasion or anti-forensic activity.

Examples of suspicious behavior:
- Stopping security services
- Disabling Microsoft Defender
- Disabling Sysmon logging
- Modifying Windows Firewall settings
- Removing or altering security monitoring configurations


Investigation commands:
Verify authorized activity --> Identify users responsible --> Review events preceding the log clearing action --> Investigate for signs of privelege escalation, persistence, or malicious execution --> Determine wheter additional security controls were disabled

Alert Concept: Windows Security Log Clearing
Description: Detects instances where Windows Security Event Logs have been cleared, potentially indicating an attempt to remove evidence of malicious activity or evade defensive mechanisms

Trigger Condition: One or more occurences of Event ID 1102 detected in Windows Event Security Logs 
Severity: HIGH


